statement:
Let

\[A = \begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0 & 0 \\
0 & a & 0 \\
0 & 0 & 2
\end{bmatrix}\]

where \emph{a} is a real number.

\textbf{(d)} Sketch a graph of \emph{cond(A)} as a function of \emph{a}
for \emph{-$\infty$ \textless{} a \textless{} $\infty$}

sols:
For convenience, let's recall our results from
\href{Science:Math_Exam_Resources/Courses/MATH307/December_2010/Question_01_(b)}{part
(b)} and
\href{Science:Math_Exam_Resources/Courses/MATH307/December_2010/Question_01_(c)}{part(c)}:

\begin{align*}
\mathrm{cond}(A) &= \|A\|\|A^{-1}\| = \max\{1, |a|, 2\}\max\{1, 1/|a|, 1/2\} \\
&= \max\{|a|, 2\}\max\{1, 1/|a|\}
\end{align*}

and \emph{cond(A)} is not defined when \emph{a = 0}. This suggests
considering three cases for $\displaystyle |a|$:

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  Case 1: If $0 < |a| \leq 1$ then
\end{itemize}

\[\displaystyle
\mathrm{cond}(A) = (2)(1/|a|) = 2/|a|\]

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  Case 2: If $1 \leq |a| \leq 2$ then
\end{itemize}

\[\displaystyle
\mathrm{cond}(A) = (2)(1) = 2\]

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  Case 3: If $2 \leq |a|$ then
\end{itemize}

\[\displaystyle
\mathrm{cond}(A) = |a|(1) = |a|\]

So, the sketch looks like this:

